briefdescription.para: Returns component-wise multiplication of vectors v1 and v2.
Returns component-wise quotient of vectors v1 and v2.
Returns the dot (inner) product of two vectors.
Returns the geometric length of v.
Normalizes *v in place to unit length, returning the length before normalization.

detaileddescription.para: If the length of *v is smaller than eps then *v is set to *v/eps. The original length of *v is returned.

briefdescription.para: Returns a normalized (unit-length) vector with the same direction as v.

detaileddescription.para: If the length of this vector is smaller than eps, the vector divided by eps is returned.

briefdescription.para: Returns the projection of a onto b.
Returns the orthogonal complement of a.GetProjection(b).
Tests for equality within a given tolerance, returning true if the length of the difference vector is less than or equal to tolerance.
